<li id="cite_note-39"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-39">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">In the early 1980s, Australian fashion designer, <a href="/wiki/Maggie_Tabberer" title="Maggie Tabberer">Maggie T</a>, was the recipient of a Hoover Award for a segmentation study which showed that women with dress size 16+ underspent on clothes because they were unable to find suitable garments. This insight led to the establishment of 'plus-sized' fashion outlets. Case study reported in <i>Australian Marketing Projects: the Hoover Award for Marketing,</i> West Ryde, Australia, 1982</span>
</li>
